texts.text: "End... Everything...!"
>You sense something beyond the spirits' voices,
>and momentarily pause your attacks against them.
>You then hear a mysterious voice whisper in your head.
Heed them. The voices next to them that seek salvation...
Listen carefully.
Look carefully.
>You close your eyes and listen very carefully.
>You then begin to hear pained voices that were not audible before.
>You try to look more carefully, but nothing changes with the spirits.
>However, you begin to hear pained voices that were not audible before.
"No... Daddy... Please don't hit me...!"
"Mommy, help...! Why aren't you looking...?"
"Everyone bullies me because my eyes are a different color..."
"I'm all alone because of that..."
"Food... I need food for my child...!"
"Please, let me go...! I promise to pay you back...!"
>You also start hearing a voice come from elsewhere.
I'm doing this because you misbehaved!
It's your fault for not being a real person. It's all your fault.
You can't steal anything for any reason!
>The voices of the spirits turn from hate to despair...
"Please... Please be nice to me..."
"Why me...? Why only me...?"
"Someone... Please help me..."
>The voices of the spirits then...
"There's no place for me in this world..."
"I don't want to live anymore..."
"This world can go to hell..."
>The voices turn malicious...
Hey, Newbie! What the hell's up with you?!
You'll seriously get killed if you don't stay focused!
Get back here already!
>You return to your senses after hearing their voices.
"This world should just end..."
>What you actually see hasn't changed at all,
>and only the cursing spirits remain in your field of view.
>Then where did those voices seeking help come from?
I'm hallucinating.
I wasn't hallucinating.
>But they were too pained to sound like hallucinations.
>What if those voices were what the spirits were really saying...?
>Maybe those voices were coming from those spirits...?
>You begin to dig deeper into your questions.
>Where did all this malice come from...?
>This world is supposedly drowning in malice.
>Does that mean everyone everywhere is feeling this way?
>Fighting this malice only produces more malice.
>No, wait... Malice grows because...
We antagonize it.
We don't listen.
>Because we try to ignore the cries for help without understanding them first.
>That turns into a far greater despair and festers in the form of malice.
>If that's the case, these spirits really are...
"Die!"
>A spirit attacks you...!
*Wince*
>You take the attack head-on and are hurt badly.
Newbie!! Yo, seriously! What the fuck is up with you today?!
I'm coming to help! Try to hold them off!
>But you do not hear them at all,
>and drop your phone out of exhaustion...
[sys user_name]!!
"Die... Die...!"
>Hearing these voices
>makes you tear up for some reason.
>How can you save them...?
>More spirits begin attacking you.
>And you sit there and take it all...
Newbie!!!
>The spirits all continue to gather on you.
>Everyone else's voice sounds far away.
>You let your instincts take over,
>and lovingly embrace the spirits.
What?! The spirits... They're glowing...
"Thank you... Thank you for understanding my pain..."
"I just wanted someone to listen... To actually see me..."
>The spirits begin to disappear along with their "spite".
W-What's going on...?
Wait. Can you hear that?
"It was hard... So hard..."
"That's why we were..."
Hey, these voices...
No way... These people...
They were in so much pain and had nowhere to run.
All they could do was curse this world...
Wait, that's what we were fighting against...?
Stop attacking, y'all...!
>The Liberators cease their attacks,
>Everyone's minds become filled with the pain and suffering the spirits feel.
>But the spirits in turn start to glow warmly and disappear.
>And the Aura Gate begins to fade away.
>But one voice still remains...
You have become the ones that shall rise up against Vanitas
by facing this malice and your doom.
I have spent much time calling to you.
But my voice will not reach those that antagonize this evil.
However, you began to question yourselves out of your own volition.
And arrived upon the true identity of this malice and the idea of neighborly love.
You heard my voice and the voices of these spirits
because you lent us an ear and heeded our words.
You have acquired the ability to
possibly release this world from its pain and suffering.
Who...? W-What do you mean...?
I created this Aura Gate as a test for you.
You MADE an Aura Gate?! How...?!
Alas, you were able to overcome this test.
So you were behind all of this? Why not show yourself already?
I am Maria. The one that has sought hope for humanity since time immemorial...
And I am hoping that you will be the ones that save humanity from this world's malice...
>This voice was the one you were hearing all this time...
